cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with the problem of 3D object pose estimation in RGB images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves learning correspondences between RGB images and rendered depth images of CAD models, which requires a combination of geometric reasoning and machine learning techniques. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to robotics (cs.RO), where object pose estimation is an important task for manipulation and grasping. The use of a deep quadruplet convolutional neural network for joint learning of keypoints and descriptors indicates that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to graphics (cs.GR), as it involves rendering CAD models and establishing 2D-3D correspondences.
